.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="44FFB0EAFFA7FFBA158BF839B74EFD25" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="238" pageId="12" pageNumber="237" type="description">
<paragraph id="0C5AE361FFA7FFBA158BF839B326FF01" blockId="12.[151,1436,1940,2039]" lastBlockId="13.[151,1437,151,1077]" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="238" pageId="12" pageNumber="237">Crown medially little shorter than next to eyes, more than 7× as wide between eyes as long medially, transversely depressed, transition to face rimmed. Face with lateral frontal sutures slightly convex in basal half; distance between antennae about 3.8 as wide as apex of frontoclypeus. Clypellus widened apically. Pronotum about 2.6× as wide as median length. Forewings without cross veins between claval veins. Fore tibiae not expanded.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0C5AE361FFA6FFBA158BFF5EB4B1FDE9" blockId="13.[151,1437,151,1077]" pageId="13" pageNumber="238">
<emphasis id="3E913F73FFA6FFBA158BFF5EB75AFF2D" box="[199,365,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="238">Male genitalia</emphasis>
. Pygofer about 1.5× as long as basal height in lateral view, basal half broad then abruptly narrowed then gradually to conically rounded apex, with spine-like process arising from ventral margin, dorsal half of ventral margin serrated before the origin of the process; a few macrosetae present in distal 0.33. Valve with anterior margin convex, about 3.3 times as wide as long medially. Subgenital plate, elongate, triangular, about 2.7 × as long as basal width, distal half a membranous appendix. Style with well-developed subapical lobe, apophysis curved laterally, apex narrowed and surface transversely striate. Connective with broad, quadrangular stem, about as long as arms, anterior margin without median lobe. Aedeagus with shaft more or less of uniform width in lateral view with lateral processes at base, widely separated at base, about as wide as shaft at midlength with their apices divergent in dorsal and ventral views, slightly shorter than shaft; dorsal apodeme well-developed, slightly more than half length of shaft; gonopore apical on ventral surface.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0C5AE361FFA6FFBA158BFDC6B23EFD51" blockId="13.[151,1437,151,1077]" pageId="13" pageNumber="238">
<emphasis id="3E913F73FFA6FFBA158BFDC6B7C3FDB4" box="[199,500,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="238">Female pregenital sternite</emphasis>
. Sternite VII about 1.75 as wide as long medially, Posterior margin sinuate, with lateral angles slightly produced posteriorly; medially dark brown in distal half.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0C5AE361FFA6FFBA158BFD0EB74EFD25" blockId="13.[151,1437,151,1077]" pageId="13" pageNumber="238">
<emphasis id="3E913F73FFA6FFBA158BFD0EB75EFD7C" box="[199,361,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="238">Measurements</emphasis>
. Male 
<quantity id="CB1D4E84FFA6FFBA14F1FD0EB471FD7D" box="[445,582,655,681]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.3" metricValueMax="8.4" metricValueMin="8.2" pageId="13" pageNumber="238" unit="mm" value="8.3" valueMax="8.4" valueMin="8.2">8.2–8.4 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="CB1D4E84FFA6FFBA17DDFD0EB52DFD7D" box="[657,794,655,681]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8499999999999996" metricValueMax="2.9" metricValueMin="2.8" pageId="13" pageNumber="238" unit="mm" value="2.8499999999999996" valueMax="2.9" valueMin="2.8">2.8–2.9 mm</quantity>
wide across eyes and 
<quantity id="CB1D4E84FFA6FFBA1153FD0FB29FFD7D" box="[1055,1192,654,681]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.55" metricValueMax="2.6" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="13" pageNumber="238" unit="mm" value="2.55" valueMax="2.6" valueMin="2.5">2.5–2.6 mm</quantity>
wide across posterolateral angles of pronotum. Female 
<quantity id="CB1D4E84FFA6FFBA1765FD32B448FD19" box="[553,639,691,717]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.8" pageId="13" pageNumber="238" unit="mm" value="8.8">8.8 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="CB1D4E84FFA6FFBA178BFD32B529FD19" box="[711,798,691,717]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="13" pageNumber="238" unit="mm" value="3.2">3.2 mm</quantity>
wide across eyes and 
<quantity id="CB1D4E84FFA6FFBA1156FD32B246FD19" box="[1050,1137,691,717]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.9" pageId="13" pageNumber="238" unit="mm" value="2.9">2.9 mm</quantity>
wide across posterolateral angles of pronotum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
